'''Communication satellites''', also known as '''comsats''', were a form of high-bandwidth relays that were used for communication between two points that were at a large distance.

During the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation's]] [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|invasion of Naboo]], they used slave satellites to amplify the signal from [[Lucrehulk-class battleship/Legends|Droid Control Ships]].

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], [[Ansible Inc.|Ansible Incorporated]] manufactured several different models of communication [[Satellite/Legends|satellite]] that came into widespread use throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].

The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] maintained a vast network of communications satellites used for surveillance with each satellite linked to the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] in [[Galactic City/Legends|Imperial City]]. The network allowed Imperial Security to monitor and control the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]] and other territories of the Empire. At its peak, the network spanned as far as the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. Satellites were often hidden in [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] fields or by uninhabited planets and were usually protected by [[Space mine/Legends|mines]]. Destruction of surveillance satellites was actively pursued by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] as a means to disrupt Imperial control.

The Rebels used some communications satellites, [[Battle of Orron III|stolen]] from [[Orron III]], to help them intercept Imperial transmissions while attempting to learn more about the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star I]].

